People Involved
Special Skills Required
Duration
Information
Tools and Safety Equipment
RISK Probability Severity Risk
Estimation Probability Consequence Residual
Risk
Manual handling risks: others Remote Minor I Remote Minor I
Mechanical hazards: Struck against Remote Concerning II Remote Minor I
Manual handling risks: lifting, transport Remote Fatal III Remote Minor I
RELEVANT ASPECTS TIME
The proper functioning of the 
machine's safety devices is essential 
for safe operation. If someone 
bypasses them and forgets to put 
them back in place correctly, this will 
cause the machine to malfunction 
and create an unsafe situation.
2 min
3 min
Edited by Revised by
John Doe Ingrid Gonzalez
Bypassing Safety Devices
To avoid potential accidents caused by safety devices being mistakenly bypassed.
All machines
After each changeover
Maintenance and Engineering Technicians
2. BYPASSING SECURITY DEVICES IS STRICTLY
